import numpy as np
iris_setosa=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-setosa']
iris_virginica=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-virginica']
iris_versicolor=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-versicolor']

plt.plot(iris_setosa["petal_length"],np.zeros_like(iris_setosa['petal_length']),'o')
plt.plot(iris_virginica["petal_length"],np.zeros_like(iris_virginica['petal_length']),'v')
plt.plot(iris_versicolor["petal_length"],np.zeros_like(iris_versicolor['petal_length']),'*')

plt.show()
In [24]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming 'iris' DataFrame is already defined
species = ['Iris-setosa', 'Iris-virginica', 'Iris-versicolor']
markers = ['o', 'v', '*']

for sp, marker in zip(species, markers):
    species_data = iris.loc[iris['species'] == sp]
    plt.plot(species_data["petal_length"], np.zeros_like(species_data['petal_length']), marker, label=sp)

plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [26]:
import numpy as np
iris_setosa=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-setosa']
iris_virginica=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-virginica']
iris_versicolor=iris.loc[iris['species']=='Iris-versicolor']

for i in iris.columns[:-1]:

    plt.plot(iris_setosa[i],np.zeros_like(iris_setosa[i]),'o')
    plt.plot(iris_virginica[i],np.zeros_like(iris_virginica[i]),'v')
    plt.plot(iris_versicolor[i],np.zeros_like(iris_versicolor[i]),'*')
    plt.xlabel(str(i))
    plt.show()

for i in iris.columns:
    counts,bin_edges=np.histogram(iris_setosa['petal_length'],bins=10,density=True)

    pdf=counts/(sum(counts))
    print(pdf)
    print(bin_edges)
    cdf=np.cumsum(pdf)
    plt.plot(bin_edges[1:],pdf)
    plt.plot(bin_edges[1:],cdf)
